{{main|2024 Summer Olympics torch relay}}
]]
The Olympic torch relay began with the lighting of the Olympic flame on 16&nbsp;April in Olympia, Greece|Olympia, Greece, 100 days before the start of the Games. Greek rower Stefanos Douskos was the first torchbearer and swimmer Laure Manaudou served as the first French torchbearer. The latter was selected to be one of four captains of the torch relay, alongside swimmer Florent Manaudou (her brother), paratriathlete {{ill|Mona Francis|fr}}, and para-athlete Dimitri Pavadé. The torch relay was expected to have 10,000 torchbearers and visit over 400 settlements in 65 French territories, including six Overseas France|overseas.
